{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770322126,"nonce":"nPrdQ9DR8ZwbbNqpqcPD3uxoqE4=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87oqNEX","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/173","origin":"github"},"title":"Create agent code review checklist for script modifications","message":"## Problem\n\nWhen modifying scripts, important steps are often missed:\n- Code duplication (PR #171 initially duplicated bootstrap logic)\n- Legacy code removal (legacy `configs/*.repos` support lingered)\n- Documentation updates (done as afterthought, not part of initial work)\n\n## Solution\n\nCreate a code review checklist specifically for agents modifying scripts.\n\n## Implementation\n\nCreate `.agent/checklists/SCRIPT_MODIFICATION.md`:\n\n```markdown\n# Script Modification Checklist\n\nBefore committing changes to scripts in `.agent/scripts/`:\n\n## Code Quality\n- [ ] No duplicated logic (extract functions if needed)\n- [ ] Legacy code paths removed (not just bypassed)\n- [ ] Error messages are helpful and accurate\n- [ ] Temp files properly cleaned up (use traps)\n\n## Documentation\n- [ ] Script header comment updated\n- [ ] README.md updated if usage changed\n- [ ] Example commands in docs still work\n- [ ] QUICKSTART.md updated if workflow changed\n\n## Testing\n- [ ] Syntax check: \\`bash -n script.sh\\`\n- [ ] Tested happy path manually\n- [ ] Tested error conditions\n\n## Legacy Cleanup\n- [ ] Checked for unused fallback code paths\n- [ ] Removed support for deprecated patterns\n- [ ] Updated all docs mentioning old behavior\n```\n\nAgents should reference this checklist in PR descriptions.\n\n## Benefits\n\n- Systematic approach prevents missed steps\n- Self-documenting process\n- Higher quality initial commits","files":null}]}